The article discusses the benefits of tax reform, particularly in relation to corporate taxes. It argues that by closing loopholes and reducing tax rates, tax reform will encourage corporations to prioritize productive activities over unproductive ones aimed at minimizing tax exposure. The current high corporate tax rate in the US leads to companies spending excessive time and money on avoiding taxes and keeping profits overseas. Tax reform would remove incentives for this behavior and increase corporate investment within America, leading to new opportunities for growth and success against foreign competitors.